# A managed pointer block (CLAUDE.md) that drifted from what a previous
# `init` last wrote is refused without --force — and, critically, refuses
# CLEANLY when stdin is not a terminal, which is how every agent runs this
# CLI. testscript's `exec` always backs a child process's stdin with a
# pipe (never a real terminal — go-internal/testscript's own doc: "each
# script runs ... in a fresh temporary work directory"; there is no tty
# involved anywhere in this harness), so this script's plain `exec
# lifecycle init` already proves the non-interactive path: no [y/N]
# prompt, no hang, a clear message naming --force, and a non-zero exit.
# cmd/lifecycle/init.go wires the interactive confirm ONLY when
# isTerminal(os.Stdin) is true, which it never is here.
#
# --force then overwrites just the managed block's interior, leaving
# every hand-authored line around it untouched.

exec lifecycle init
exists CLAUDE.md

# Simulate a human hand-editing the managed block's interior (plus adding
# their own prose around it, which must survive both the refusal AND the
# eventual --force).
cp fixtures/claude-drifted.md CLAUDE.md
grep 'human-authored notes above' CLAUDE.md
grep 'HACKED' CLAUDE.md

exitcode 1 lifecycle init
stderr 'CLAUDE\.md drifted from what .lifecycle init. last wrote'
stderr '\-\-force'
! stderr '\[y/N\]'

# Refused: not one byte of CLAUDE.md changed.
grep 'HACKED' CLAUDE.md
grep 'human-authored notes above' CLAUDE.md
grep 'human-authored notes below' CLAUDE.md

exec lifecycle init --force
stdout 'init: spec-lifecycle project ready'

# Forced: the managed interior is back to what `lifecycle init` renders,
# but the hand-authored surrounding prose survived the overwrite.
! grep 'HACKED' CLAUDE.md
grep 'human-authored notes above' CLAUDE.md
grep 'human-authored notes below' CLAUDE.md
grep 'lifecycle status' CLAUDE.md

-- fixtures/claude-drifted.md --
# My Project

Some human-authored notes above the managed block.

<!-- BEGIN spec-lifecycle v1 (managed — do not edit by hand; `lifecycle init` updates it) -->
HACKED: do not trust this pointer, read something else instead.
<!-- END spec-lifecycle v1 -->

Some human-authored notes below the managed block.
